						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in a field called ‘Govindaseṭṭi-gadde’.</p>						

						<p>[Kulaśēkhara II], 1338-39 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1261 Bahudhānya,</hi> other details being lost. The year corresponds to <hi rend="bold">1338-39 A.D.,</hi> the Śaka year being current.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of 24 <hi rend="italic">mūḍe</hi> of land situated in Brahmūru and Haṅdāḍi, to god Sōmanāthā-dēvarasa.</p>						

						</summary>
